app.cards.game

Class CardSequence

  • java.lang.Object
    • app.cards.game.CardSequence
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Set<Card>>

     class CardSequence
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Set<Card>>

    A CardSequence encapsulates a list of Card object with consecutive Ranks.

    More specifically, each position in the list can take a Set of Cards with equal rank. The Set at the next position in the list then contains cards of the next highest rank and so on. A valid CardSequence could look like the following (each Set is grouped in square brackets):

    [[6s], [7h, 7s], [8c], [9d, 9h]]

    A CardSequence object can then be used as the basis for Straight detection.
